- Add AuthMonitor routines for generating a deprecated key type for
testing with "old"/not-upgraded clients.
- Add tests for expected service key upgrades by MON/OSD/MDS.
- Add warnings if the service key is still using the insecure/old key
type. With tests.
- Add (silenceable) warnings if a service daemon is still
authenticating with an insecure/old key type.
- Add (silenceable) warnings if clients are authenticating with
insecure/old key types. With tests.
- Documentation for how to rotate authentication keys (for service or
client). Also how to restrict key types allowed for service or
authentication keys. (This will be done via a Ceph config.)
